Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.29,0:00:21.12,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A courageous heart and deduction power!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.12,0:00:23.12,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The rhythm that leads us to the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.12,0:00:25.00,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Full suspense, part two!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.00,0:00:26.96,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An unexpected culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.96,0:00:28.54,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Recognizing that one truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.54,0:00:30.38,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A child with the mind of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.42,0:00:32.63,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.70,0:01:46.29,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}While we were driving near the ocean, our car broke down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.75,0:01:51.88,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We stayed at lawyer Tachibana's villa for one night.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.21,0:01:54.46,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}However, the next day...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.09,0:01:56.38,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Right in front of our eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.34,0:02:02.39,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Mr. Tachibana's boat capsized and he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.60,0:02:11.69,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We found out that Mr. Tachibana was killed by someone with the initials T.K., who had been sending threats to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.02,0:02:16.07,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Five years ago, Mr. Tachibana acquitted him of a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.07,0:02:21.28,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We thought he was Tatsuya Kumada,\Nso we rushed into his apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.62,0:02:23.83,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But what we saw was...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.66,0:02:27.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kumada{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, we're coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.50,0:02:36.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}W-What is this...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.84,0:02:38.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kumada, the suspect...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.13,0:02:41.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Suicide!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.26,0:02:49.02,Title,Sign,0,0,0,,The Bay of Revenge\N(Part 2)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.39,0:02:50.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please stay back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.39,0:02:52.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, stay back!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.48,0:02:57.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems like he used this chair to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.82,0:03:01.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's an odd way to hang the rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.91,0:03:04.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's tied to the veranda handrail.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.62,0:03:10.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it because his feet would touch the floor\Nif the rope was hung from the beam?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.17,0:03:18.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, there was a loud noise from the room upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.26,0:03:21.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard a thud, as if something fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.93,0:03:23.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It only happened once, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.97,0:03:25.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.10,0:03:28.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was after 7:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.39,0:03:33.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The estimated time of death is between\N6:00 and 7:00, so it makes sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.52,0:03:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Around 7:00?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.94,0:03:41.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I wasn't home. I came home at 7:15.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.78,0:03:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.36,0:03:44.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.82,0:03:48.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I came home, I heard the washing\Nmachine from Kumada{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.08,0:03:52.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.29,0:03:52.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.67,0:03:57.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would someone who is about to\Ncommit suicide wash their clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.75,0:04:00.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.68,0:04:06.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.51,0:04:08.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's dangerous! What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.89,0:04:10.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ahh, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.06,0:04:14.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which boat was Tachibana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.77,0:04:16.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the one on the far right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.86,0:04:18.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can I see it for a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.86,0:04:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, are you investigating the crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.78,0:04:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh. I'm a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.41,0:04:29.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your hard work!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.33,0:04:33.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What are these scratches?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.08,0:04:36.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.71,0:04:39.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were these scratches here before?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.50,0:04:43.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're new! That's the first time I've ever seen them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.51,0:04:47.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tachibana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} or the police probably did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.64,0:04:49.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.35,0:04:55.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stolen boat was found, but the anchor\Nwas stolen and it's a great deal of trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.52,0:04:56.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anchor?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.85,0:04:57.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.23,0:05:01.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you fish, you use it so you won't float away with the tide.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.69,0:05:04.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sink this weight to the bottom of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.07,0:05:09.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He took away the wire from the big boat, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.74,0:05:12.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.04,0:05:15.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It still hasn't been found?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.66,0:05:20.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't found anywhere in or near the boat this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.79,0:05:24.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That boat's anchor was gone, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.38,0:05:27.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.52,0:05:35.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.18,0:05:37.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.52,0:05:39.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan! Where were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.02,0:05:41.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You too, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.57,0:05:43.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What were you doing with Sakuraba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.03,0:05:45.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cleaning, of course, cleaning!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.74,0:05:48.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakuraba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} just came back from walking Yohan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.32,0:05:51.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakuraba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.74,0:05:56.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was the case with Tatsuya Kumada five years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.66,0:05:59.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, it's confidential.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.79,0:06:04.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.38,0:06:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sugimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Where were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.22,0:06:09.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Vacation!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.34,0:06:11.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was watching the news and left during the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.60,0:06:13.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.97,0:06:16.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, is the culprit TK?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.77,0:06:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.77,0:06:21.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know Tatsuya Kumada?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.73,0:06:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, his real name is revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.78,0:06:27.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He held a high position in the securities company.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.90,0:06:31.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masahiko Tsuruta, who worked under\Nhim, used the money for his own use.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.28,0:06:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was caught, so he committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.99,0:06:39.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, from Tsuruta's diary, we found out that\NKumada was the one embezzling the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.04,0:06:43.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thus, Kumada was charged for murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.13,0:06:51.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the people living under Masahiko Tsuruta's\Napartment heard something fall at 10:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.34,0:06:55.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, Kumada was at a karaoke party.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.10,0:07:02.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The alibi was proved, and Kumada was innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.52,0:07:05.61,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then it's just like this case!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.53,0:07:07.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sugimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.36,0:07:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You came three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.45,0:07:12.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would you know about the case from five years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.95,0:07:19.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was only looking up the threatener,\NTK, and a little about Mrs. Tachibana.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.20,0:07:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard it was Sensei's fault your father committed suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.25,0:07:32.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must of hated him, to the point where you wanted to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.72,0:07:33.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.18,0:07:39.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You are using a lot of the office's money.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.72,0:07:42.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he found out, you killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.94,0:07:44.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.32,0:07:50.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.24,0:07:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How was it, Professor?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.11,0:07:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I found out where he lived at the time the trial was held.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.16,0:07:58.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's in the same Chiba prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.58,0:08:07.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masahiko Tsuruta's family consists of his mother,\NTamiko, and his younger brother, Katsuhiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.92,0:08:09.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mother and brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.64,0:08:24.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandma!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.19,0:08:27.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know Masahiko Tsuruta's house?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.77,0:08:30.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masahiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.03,0:08:32.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.32,0:08:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even if you go, no one will be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.03,0:08:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.53,0:08:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His mother, Tamiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and his brother, Katsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r},\Nboth moved because of that incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.37,0:08:47.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He went to some school in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.96,0:08:50.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was an outstanding child.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.75,0:08:54.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The house is in a place like this, which is the reason why it won't sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.17,0:09:01.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They sometimes come to clean the house,\Nbut it's been a year since they last did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.28,0:09:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Johann...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.45,0:09:23.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.20,0:09:25.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's how it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.92,0:09:39.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The same sleeping pill in Tachibana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nwas found in Kumada's blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.10,0:09:42.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was also in the whiskey bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.39,0:09:46.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have concluded that he murdered Tachibana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.31,0:09:50.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then committed suicide by taking sleeping pills.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.56,0:09:52.23,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Crap, when did he—!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.36,0:09:54.11,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.69,0:09:57.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, here, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.36,0:10:00.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.32,0:10:03.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's this file. What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.91,0:10:06.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's an account book.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.42,0:10:14.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard the famous detective's deduction will start?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.13,0:10:18.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you going to deduce now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.97,0:10:22.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, everyone, please take a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.76,0:10:28.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will reveal the truth of Mr. Tachibana and Tatsuya Kumada.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.77,0:10:31.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.02,0:10:32.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought it was already solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.90,0:10:36.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying the conclusion we drew was wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.78,0:10:37.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.03,0:10:44.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuya Kumada was murdered by the same\Nperson who murdered Mr. Tachibana.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.70,0:10:48.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the killer is here with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.87,0:10:52.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.67,0:10:55.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let us discuss that right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.13,0:11:06.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The same sleeping pill in Mr. Tachibana's\Nbody was found in Kumada{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.10,0:11:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that after the culprit murdered Tachibana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, he did the same thing to Kumada{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.44,0:11:17.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit killed Kumada{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} while he was\Nasleep and made it look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.07,0:11:21.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is there anyone who would have been able to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.36,0:11:24.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were three people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.03,0:11:26.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yaeko Kamei.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.78,0:11:28.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuuichi Sakuraba.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.66,0:11:31.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Tachibana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.00,0:11:37.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Yaeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was there with us when the boat capsized.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.96,0:11:39.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.09,0:11:42.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.09,0:11:44.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was at the office in Tokyo when that happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.80,0:11:45.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.76,0:11:49.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter where you were when the boat capsized.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.27,0:11:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Long before Tachibana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered, the culprit was ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.90,0:11:58.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All he had to do was wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.69,0:12:00.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.19,0:12:02.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.36,0:12:03.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person we saw!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.70,0:12:07.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person on the boat with the red cap!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.79,0:12:09.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.87,0:12:11.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.00,0:12:17.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that was two hours before the boat capsized.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.88,0:12:21.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did he get the boat to turn over?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.55,0:12:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you think about why the culprit did what\Nthey did yesterday, you will understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.14,0:12:30.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you're aware, a spring tide occurred yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.31,0:12:34.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's true. With the spring tide, it was difficult to investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.31,0:12:36.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.85,0:12:43.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Spring tides exhibit a very large change\Nin sea level between high and low tides.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.03,0:12:41.05,Signs,,0,0,0,,{TODO}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.74,0:12:44.13,Signs,,0,0,0,,{TODO}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.82,0:12:47.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the crime was committed yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.20,0:12:51.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please elaborate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.62,0:12:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The guy that we saw in the red baseball cap...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.87,0:13:03.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After getting close to Tachibana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, he\Npulled off Tachibana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s life jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.63,0:13:07.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He dropped the anchor that he stole into the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.97,0:13:14.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then secured a hook that was tied\Nat the end of the rope onto the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.35,0:13:18.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way, when the high tide comes and the water level rises,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.40,0:13:21.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the boat will be pulled by the anchor and will flip over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.44,0:13:26.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After it flipped, the hook came off and\Nsank to the bottom of the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.86,0:13:32.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tachibana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who fell into the ocean, drowned.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.58,0:13:35.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't think of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.58,0:13:40.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We heard that an anchor was also stolen from the boat rental place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.13,0:13:44.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the missing anchor on the stolen boat...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.13,0:13:46.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.42,0:13:50.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That anchor is probably at the bottom of the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.39,0:13:55.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the incident, the ocean floor should have been investigated.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.73,0:13:58.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! I will contact them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.56,0:14:02.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could someone do something so cruel...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.11,0:14:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything was done to create an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.74,0:14:10.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to create an alibi at the time the boat capsized,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.82,0:14:13.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he went this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.04,0:14:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.54,0:14:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.87,0:14:18.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the anchor was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.92,0:14:20.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was on the ocean floor at the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.46,0:14:24.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We are confirming this information\Nwith the man from the rental store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.25,0:14:28.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there was a hook at the end of the rope!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.51,0:14:31.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moving on...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.30,0:14:39.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After returning to the shore, the culprit left the hat\Non the boat to leave suspicions on Kumada.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.77,0:14:44.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to the investigations, that\Nhat belonged to Kumada himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.69,0:14:48.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one else's hairs were detected.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.20,0:14:52.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hat used for disguise was probably something similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.16,0:15:00.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real hat was probably something the\Nculprit took when he met with Kumada.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.25,0:15:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kumada and the culprit were acquaintanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.75,0:15:12.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For proof, the culprit was able to go to his apartment\Nand feed him whiskey and sleeping pills.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.89,0:15:18.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He moved Kumada to the sliding door\Nand tied a rope around his neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.89,0:15:25.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, he used the railing to tie the rope hung\Nfrom the beam, pulling Kumada up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.98,0:15:33.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, he tied the rope to the railing, opened\Nthe door, and placed a chair beneath his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.86,0:15:35.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.78,0:15:41.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what about the noise that the people downstairs heard at 7:00?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.25,0:15:43.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone has an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.17,0:15:47.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, you don't need an alibi at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.80,0:15:51.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.55,0:15:58.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This trick was used five years ago when Tatsuya\NKumada killed Masahiko Tsuruta.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.27,0:16:00.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.77,0:16:04.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The washing machine that was running after 7:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.48,0:16:11.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit tied a string around the motor so it would wind up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.99,0:16:16.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He placed a loop around a chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.57,0:16:19.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he set the time on the washing machine to 7:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.45,0:16:26.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The string would spin with the motor, and thus, the chair would fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.59,0:16:31.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll have people search the washing machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.88,0:16:36.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would mean Tachibana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered at 1:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.64,0:16:41.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since Kumada's estimated time of death was from 6:00 to 7:30...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.68,0:16:44.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before 7:00, after 6:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.60,0:16:50.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who doesn't have an alibi at this time is the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.44,0:16:52.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakuraba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.48,0:16:56.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You left here at 1:00 and came back after 7:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.24,0:16:58.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.12,0:17:01.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Many people hated Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.12,0:17:05.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you even checked everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.21,0:17:07.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakuraba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.63,0:17:09.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you come to get at the office yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.29,0:17:13.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right when the boat capsized.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.38,0:17:14.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.05,0:17:15.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.05,0:17:17.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.68,0:17:20.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakuraba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it's for these account books, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.93,0:17:26.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to make it look like Sugimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} stole money\Nfrom the office, you were planning to make stuff up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.14,0:17:28.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.48,0:17:30.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.65,0:17:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last night, Sensei and I changed the content of those books.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.98,0:17:38.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were going to blame Sensei's spendings on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.78,0:17:42.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'm relieved that Sensei died...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.95,0:17:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakuraba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.24,0:17:46.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean you're "relieved"!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.71,0:17:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sick of helping Sensei do evil work!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.38,0:17:55.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said, "If you don't listen to me, you won't\Nbe able to become a lawyer in the future!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.80,0:17:58.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He threatened me. I couldn't take it anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.84,0:18:01.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakuraba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, tell us the rest at the police station.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.80,0:18:03.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.77,0:18:07.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you resist, we'll arrest you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.43,0:18:08.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.60,0:18:11.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did not kill neither Kumada nor Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.48,0:18:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.11,0:18:15.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.24,0:18:18.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't Sakuraba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.24,0:18:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I killed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.78,0:18:24.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.04,0:18:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yaeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.29,0:18:29.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was waiting for those words.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.21,0:18:34.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't silently watch others being blamed for your own crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.84,0:18:40.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were able to add sleeping pills to Sensei's water bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.76,0:18:46.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That day, after we had left, you disguised as\NKumada and left through the back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.47,0:18:49.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You used a boat to go to Tachibana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.85,0:18:55.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, you watched Tachibana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s boat capsize with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.69,0:19:03.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later that evening, Yaeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went shopping\Nand parked her car in the parking lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.78,0:19:08.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She immediately disguised somewhere and\Ntook a train to Kumada's apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.75,0:19:09.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.25,0:19:14.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.71,0:19:20.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan found this nameplate in Masahiko Tsuruta's yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.05,0:19:22.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Johann?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.84,0:19:23.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.80,0:19:26.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In German, it would be "Yohan."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.39,0:19:33.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is probably the name your son\Nwho graduated in Germany gave.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.48,0:19:34.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.02,0:19:36.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tamiko Tsuruta?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.48,0:19:39.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.15,0:19:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then Yaeko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.20,0:19:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.24,0:19:47.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She is Masahiko Tsuruta's mother, who was murdered by Kumada.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.16,0:19:53.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should have realized this earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.54,0:19:59.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yesterday at the cape, Yohan was chasing\Nafter the boat you were on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.17,0:20:04.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though you were disguised, Yohan recognized you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.55,0:20:08.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My second son died last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.76,0:20:10.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right now, Yohan is my only family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.68,0:20:15.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I lied, saying he was a stray dog, and we started living here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.81,0:20:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I fought so many times at court, but no one noticed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.65,0:20:26.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The court's decision was unfair. I grew old because of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.95,0:20:32.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then half a year ago, Kumada finally appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.79,0:20:37.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I overheard the washing machine trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.83,0:20:44.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In jail, Kumada said he would pay any amount of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.51,0:20:52.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though Sensei knew that Kumada murdered Masahiko, he acquitted Kumada of the crime for money.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.85,0:20:57.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That day, I followed Kumada to his apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.06,0:21:01.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With his hat that he left, I thought of this crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.78,0:21:08.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the threats that looked like they were from Kumada...\Nyou were sending them to Tachibana{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.66,0:21:09.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.83,0:21:12.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since yesterday, I have been so scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.74,0:21:14.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm finally relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.08,0:21:19.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were prepared to be arrested from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.42,0:21:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why, despite the fact a detective was\Nhere, you still committed the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.09,0:21:27.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.30,0:21:32.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for causing trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.07,0:23:14.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad! What the heck?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.37,0:23:17.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just repaired... that's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.04,0:23:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When can we go back to Tokyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.25,0:23:23.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.46,0:23:24.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just this once!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.71,0:23:25.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To Tokyo!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.17,0:23:29.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe if you switched places with him, someone will stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.59,0:23:30.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.63,0:23:32.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's look at the ocean a little while longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.22,0:23:35.47,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Well, I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.81,0:23:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heeeeeeeey!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.72,0:23:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do something!
